args:
The androids turn out to be with a group called
Ex Machina whose goal is to eliminate humans.
As the prince and his friends narrowly manage
to repel them, the Ex Machina androids Eirene
and Finni are given strict orders to destroy Laxi.
Damage to left carpus section.\n2.8 percent reduction in combat strength.\n▷Laxi, the leader is on your right!◁
You're not half bad, but you're nowhere\nnear enough to take on me AND Eirene!

Looks like your motion transmitter circuit
was in the same location as ours despite
our different manufacturers. I'm going to
have you settle down for a bit.
Time to peruse your memory and learn\nwhy you have two hearts in one body.
Laxi, stop! Please! Maestro would be\nso sad to see us doing this!
LAXI! I GIVE YOU MY HEART!\nGRAAAAAAAAGH!

There are excess thoughts within me.
▷Not EXCESS thoughts.
Important ones.◁
Shut up.
It is likely that Mascula's heart merged\nwith my own and caused this glitch.\n▷Laxi, listen to me!◁
A different heart was transplanted\nto replace her broken one?
But why did the two hearts overlap?\nAnd the broken heart seems to have\nsomehow been repaired...
This situation calls for thorough analysis.\nNumbers 38 and 39, take this unit back\nto the base at once.
▷Laxi, we have to do something!◁\nI know. Let's shift modes.
Eden mode? If that memory is accurate,\nthis is not good at all!

Ambient mana concentration is dropping
precipitously. Are you telling me she's
absorbing mana and converting it into
energy? That would mean...!

*gasp*
She materialized mana in physical form!
This android really is equipped with a
mana kiln!
If we can just stop the lead unit!
Stop it! If you so much as scratch Eirene,\nI'll smash you into a million pieces!
I'll rip every component off you one-by-one\nand mash your circuits into DUUUST!
▷It can't be... Is she...?◁\nShe is exhibiting a loss of control \nvery similar to annihilation mode.
I'LL DESTROY ANYONE WHO TRIES TO\nMESS WITH EIRENE! ALL OF YOU ARE\nGOING TO DIIIIIIE!
She can't even hear me...\nI have no choice...!
On my authority as leader of the 901st,\nI order the shutdown of unit Finni!
All units, this is 901 leader.\nWithdraw and exit the battlefield.
You, android with the mana kiln.\nYour designation is Laxi, correct?
Yes. Who are all of you?\n▷You look like models from a thousand\nyears ago, but why are you fighting us?◁
We are with Ex Machina, and our mission\nremains unchanged no matter how many\nmillennia pass us by.
Said mission is the extermination of all\ndragons and the liberation of the people\nshut out from this world.
▷Liberating people?! You're running\naround the city trying to KILL them!◁
Ex Machina does not define such\nlifeforms as people.

Those who nest on the surface now consort
with dragons and warp the very world,
and all such terrestrials are to be
eliminated by Ex Machina.
▷So ＂terrestrials＂ aren't people?◁\nSorry, but all people are people. There\nmust be a bug in your processing.
I have no intention of engaging in a\ndebate with all of you. However, I can\npromise that we will meet again.
And when we do, I will have you elucidate\nupon the secrets contained in your body.
My memory contains no record of an\nandroid equipped with a mana kiln.
Anassa, is there no possibility that the\nArk could be helping the terrestrials?
Such a thing is impossible.\nYour very question is nonsensical.
However, there is no doubt this unit was\ncreated 300 years ago as a copy of us.
Even we originals don't have mana kilns.\nI find it highly unlikely that the terrestrials\nof 300 years ago had such technology.
If that technology does exist,\nit must be on the Ark.
I repeat: Your query is nonsensical.
The Sky City Ark is where people fled\nwhen exposed to the terror of dragonkind.\nIt is their final paradise.

The Ark's objective is to see both dragons
and any terrestrials affiliated with them
annihilated, thereby making the planet a
paradise for all humanoids once more.

Even if an Ark engineer manufactured
an android with an onboard mana kiln,
there is no way said android would see
fit to protect the terrestrials.
Your verbiage contains many vagaries;\nI conject there is a bug in your thought\nprocessing. Do you require maintenance?
My self-diagnostics are normal;\nI deem maintenance unnecessary.
As there are no major changes to your\noperating efficiency, I will entrust the\nmatter to your judgment.
However, there IS a unit within the 901st\nAndroid Corps whose operating efficiency\nhas dropped significantly.
I have confirmed the unit designated Finni\nrefused orders and then proceeded to\nexhibit a loss of control.
Unit Finni is one of the rare androids\nequipped with a heart, but said heart\nseems to have been damaged.
Heart technology was lost over the past\nthousand years, and not even Ex Machina\ncan construct or repair them.

Even under optimal circumstances, the
heart is a double-edged sword which can
cause unstable behavior; it is dangerous to
leave a damaged one installed in a unit.
I have determined her to be unnecessary\nto Ex Machina, and propose her disposal.
Wait! Yes, it is true that her operating\nefficiency has dropped, but Finni's\ncapabilities far surpass ordinary units.
If we hope to stand against powerful units\nlike the android with the mana kiln,\nFinni's capabilities will be critical.
Very well. I will defer final judgment.

If she can defeat the android equipped
with the mana kiln, I will revise my
perception that the unit Finni is no longer
of use to Ex Machina.
However, this deferment is temporary.\nWhen the time comes, I expect you to\nmake the correct decision.
(I can't let Finni be deactivated.\nI will do anything to stop it!)
